     "Plastic friction: sustained contact noise — high sustain_ratio, low crest, continuous flux, no single onset.",
     "Never front-loaded like IMPACT; more continuous and higher-centroid than MOVEMENT.",
     "Plastic scrape / creak / squeak: bright, rasping, and often near-tonal at the squeak extreme — harmonicity can rise well above the noise floor while staying unstable, which is why that prior is loose.",
     "Higher-centroid and grittier than RUBBER-FRICTION (a lower, rubbery squeal) and much brighter than LEATHER-CREAK.",
     "Not METAL-FRICTION: no long ringing partials, no sustained inharmonic screech tail."
